    "He stepped down as CEO in 2023 after an investigation alleged that he paid underage girls for sex. Miller denied the allegations.",
    "In 2024, he sold Future Electronics to Taiwan-based WT Microelectronics in a $3.8 billion deal, likely pocketing ten figures from the sale.",
    "Miller was arrested by Montreal police in May 2024 and charged with 21 sex crimes counts. He vowed to \"vigorously protect his reputation, fight for the truth and refute these false allegations.\"",
    "In June 2025, a Quebec Superior Court judge deemed Miller, who is suffering from Parkinson's disease, too sick to stand trial and ordered a stay of proceedings"
  ],
